  "text": "A systems approach also enables consideration of feedback loops within the system that propel cardiovascular disease morbidity and mortality. Feedback loops are the basic operating unit of a system [CITATION_1] . They are formed when changes in a variable affect a series of A SYSTEMS VIEW OF CARDIOVASCULAR DISEASE 5 related factors that eventually result in perpetuation or stabilization of the original variable.",
